au.gov.ansto.bragg.cicada.core
Interface Algorithm

All Superinterfaces:
au.gov.ansto.bragg.base.common.All, Common, au.gov.ansto.bragg.base.common.Publisher, java.io.Serializable
public interface Algorithm
extends Common

Algorithm is the interface for cicada algorithm. A cicada algorithm is a java Class that are built upon a recipe xml file. It create and manage a framework that contains multiple processors. When intialized, it builds concrete processors to process input data. The algorithm object will expose tuners, agents and sinks to upper level applications.

getTunerArray

java.util.List<Tuner> getTunerArray()
This method gets the tuner list of the algorithm. A tuner is a proxy of a VAR port. It can view and change the VAR port signal and status. A tuner is both observable and controllable.

Returns:
list of tuners

getTunerGroupList

java.util.List<java.util.List<Tuner>> getTunerGroupList()
This method returns a list of tuner list. Every processor of the algorithm has a list of tuners. Put all these list handles to a new list and return it.

Returns:
list of tuner list
